  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6584 trading below the 6596 flip in PIN regime, dealers are currently buying the dip as required hedging activity, providing strong support around the 6570 max negative gamma level. The massive positive gamma wall at 6600 (+65B) will trigger heavy dealer selling pressure on any move higher, creating a natural ceiling just 16 points above current levels. The recent GEX surge combined with the tight 6570-6600 range suggests dealers will aggressively defend both boundaries, keeping price action compressed.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect SPX to trade sideways between 6570 support and 6600 resistance with limited breakout potential.",
